Package org.cicirello.sequences

Collection of classes related to manipulating general sequences of various forms (e.g., arrays or various types, Strings, Lists).

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Sequence<E>
    A Sequence is an ordered sequence of values, similar to an array or a list, except a Sequence has a more limited, and specific set of functionality in support of algorithms such as distance metrics (among others) on sequences.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ObjectSequence<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    An ObjectSequence is a sequence of values of any one object type, provided the objects are Comparable.
    PrimitiveSequence
    A PrimitiveSequence is a sequence of values of any one of Java's eight primitive types.
    PrimitiveValue
    The PrimitiveValue class is a wrapper class for all eight of Java's primitive types.
